"a.华丽的，辉煌的 【英】 adj. 华丽的，辉煌的 (shining brilliantly) 【考】 bravura : performance / resplendent : appearance(华美的演奏/灿烂的 外表)bootless : futility / effulgent : resplendence(无用的无用/辉煌的 辉煌)反义词：dull(阴暗的 ) 【记】 re(再)+splend(发光) +ent→不断发光→辉 煌的 【例】 the resplendent rays of the sun adj. 华丽辉煌的(外表华丽耀眼的) 【记】re反复, splend闪耀, ent: 反复闪耀－辉煌的 【类】bravura: performance = resplendent: appearance华美的演奏 = 灿烂的外表bootless: futility = effulgent: resplendence无用的无用 = 辉煌的辉煌 【反】dull(adj 迟钝的; 阴暗的); lack luster(缺乏光泽) 【记】同splendid 辉煌壮丽的的 resplendent (adj.)  mid-15c., from Latin resplendentem (nominative resplendens) ""brilliant, radiant,"" present participle of resplendere ""to glitter, shine,"" from re-, intensive prefix, + splendere ""to shine, be splendid"" (see splendid). Related: Resplendently."
